                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/6095c.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Consul at Vera Cruz</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-02-11T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 11, 1913—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Repeat to Puerto Mexico, Salina Cruz, Frontera, Campeche, Progreso, and Tapachula
                    the following, which was given to the press yesterday afternoon and was
                    telegraphed to the Embassy at Mexico City:</p>
                <p>[See telegram to the Ambassador, February 10, ante.]</p>
                <p>You are instructed to be prepared to organize at once, in case there is any
                    interference with communication between Vera Cruz and Mexico City, a corp of
                    couriers or such other means of communication as it may be possible for you to
                    provide.</p>
                <p>The U. S. S. <hi rend="italic">Virginia</hi> is due to arrive at Vera Cruz about
                    February 15.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
